1️⃣ STP Loop Scenario

A user reports network slowness. You notice high CPU on switches and MAC addresses constantly moving between ports. What would you suspect and how would you investigate?

2️⃣ Root Bridge Change

After a maintenance window, traffic paths have changed and some applications are slower. How would you determine whether the STP root bridge has changed?

3️⃣ BPDU Guard Incident

An access port suddenly goes into err-disabled state after a new device is connected. What could have happened?

4️⃣ EtherChannel Not Forming

Two switches are connected with four links configured for EtherChannel, but the Port-Channel remains down. What would you check?

5️⃣ Uneven EtherChannel Traffic

A Port-Channel has four active links, but traffic seems to use only one physical link. Is this necessarily a problem? What would you verify?

6️⃣ STP Blocking Decision

Two switches are connected using two parallel links. One link is forwarding and one is blocked. How does STP decide which port gets blocked?

7️⃣ Broadcast Storm

A switch receives excessive broadcast traffic and users complain of intermittent connectivity. What Layer 2 mechanisms can help protect the network?

8️⃣ Port Security Violation

A user plugs a small unmanaged switch into a wall port and several devices connect through it. Shortly afterward the port stops working. What Layer 2 feature may have caused this?

9️⃣ DHCP Snooping Scenario

Users suddenly start receiving incorrect IP addresses after someone connects a wireless router to the network. Which Layer 2 security feature would help prevent this?

🔟 Unidirectional Link Failure

A fiber link between two switches develops a problem where traffic can pass in one direction but not the other. What Layer 2 protection feature can detect this condition?

